{"type":"message","id":"7d85bc94","parentId":"313f2b53","timestamp":"2026-03-09T17:42:50.540Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Root cause:** The QMD collection is named `memory`, but my AGENTS.md instructions had `-c openclaw-memory`. Every QMD search I ever ran was silently failing with `Collection not found` and returning nothing — which is why I could never find anything through QMD.\n\n**Fixed:**\n- ✅ Updated `AGENTS.md` — changed `-c openclaw-memory` → `-c memory` in both command templates\n- ✅ Logged the fix in `MEMORY.md` so I don't forget\n\nThis means my QMD memory recall has been **completely broken** since setup. Should work properly from now on! 🔧"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-opus-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":153,"cacheRead":23229,"cacheWrite":235,"totalTokens":23618,"cost":{"input":0.000005,"output":0.0038250000000000003,"cacheRead":0.0116145,"cacheWrite":0.00146875,"total":0.01691325}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773078165436}}
